## SSH
openssh, generate ssh key
     ssh-keygen
         
send public key to remote server
     ssh-copy-id username@remote.server

copy files frome remote server
     scp [-Pportnumber] username@remote.server:file/to/send [username@destination:]/where/to/put

## Console
let a program run in background
    program &

setup terminal proxy
    export http_proxy=socks5://127.0.0.1:1080 https_proxy=socks5://127.0.0.1:1080

## Chromium
setup chromium proxy
    chromium --proxy-server="[HTTP|Socks5]://url[:port]"

## NetworkManager
to avoid endless password prompt(for atheros chip):
    sudo echo "options ath9k nohwcrypt=1" >> /etc/modprobe.d/ath9k.conf
to connect and disconnect wifi:
    nmcli dev wifi connect "ssid" password "password"
    nmcli dev disconnect (iface?) wifi0
to enable networkmanager service:
    sytemctl enable networkmanager
   
## Switch usb mode
switch between different mode of usb stick:
   usb_modeswitch -KW -v 148f -p 2878
check the driver information:
   dmesg | grep mt7601u














